                <note rend="inline" type="source">723.2515/522: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Shea</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-11-05T14:00:00-04:42">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 5, 1919, 2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received November 6, 12.05 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The press to-day publishes, officially, a statement issued by the Ministry for
                    Foreign Affairs denying entirely that Chile had given to Bolivia an extension of
                    land north of Arica for the purpose of a seaport. The statement is issued
                    because of telegraphic report from Washington, published yesterday in the Buenos
                    Aires newspapers, stating that this cession had been officially made by the
                    Chilean Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Shea</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
